\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb3 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Today is the anniversary of the death of Leonhard Euler
\f1\b0  (1707-1783), Swiss {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematician"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 mathematician}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physicist"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 physicist}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astronomer"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 astronomer}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geographer"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 geographer}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logician"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 logician}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Engineer"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 engineer}} who made important and influential discoveries in many branches of mathematics, such as {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infinitesimal_calculus"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 infinitesimal calculus}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Graph_theory"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 graph theory}}, while also making pioneering contributions to several branches such as {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Topology"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 topology}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analytic_number_theory"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 analytic number theory}}. He also introduced much of the modern mathematical terminology and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematical_notation"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 notation}}, particularly for {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematical_analysis"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 mathematical analysis}}, such as the notion of a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Function_(mathematics)"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 mathematical function}}. He is also known for his work in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mechanics"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 mechanics}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fluid_dynamics"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 fluid dynamics}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Optics"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 optics}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astronomy"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 astronomy}} and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Music_theory"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 music theory}}.
\fs22\fsmilli11200 \cf4 \super \

\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \nosupersub \
\cb3 Euler was one of the most eminent mathematicians of the 18th century and is held to be one of the greatest in history. He is also widely considered to be the most prolific mathematician of all time. His collected works fill 92 volumes, more than anyone else in the field. He spent most of his adult life in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saint_Petersburg"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Saint Petersburg}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russian_Empire"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Russia}}, and in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Berlin"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Berlin}}, then the capital of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kingdom_of_Prussia"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Prussia}}.\cb1 \
\cb3 A statement attributed to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pierre-Simon_Laplace"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Pierre-Simon Laplace}} expresses Euler's influence on mathematics: "Read Euler, read Euler, he is the master of us all."\
In total there exist more than 860 articles of Euler and is due to him most of the mathematical modern terminology:  the greek letter pi for pi, 
\f2\i i
\f1\i0  for the imaginary unit, f(x) for function and the symbol of summation.\

\fs22\fsmilli11200 \cf4 \super \
\
\'c8 oggi l\'92anniversario della morte di Leonard Eulero, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matematico"}}{\fldrslt 
\fs28 \nosupersub matematico}}
\fs28 \cf2 \nosupersub  e {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fisico"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 fisico}} {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Svizzera"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 svizzero}}.\cb1 \
\cb3 \'c8 considerato il pi\'f9 importante {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matematico"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 matematico}} del {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/XVIII_secolo"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Settecento}}, e uno dei massimi della storia. \'c8 noto per essere tra i pi\'f9 prolifici di tutti i tempi e ha fornito contributi storicamente cruciali in svariate aree: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analisi_matematica"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 analisi infinitesimale}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Funzione_speciale"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 funzioni speciali}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meccanica_razionale"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 meccanica razionale}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meccanica_celeste"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 meccanica celeste}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Teoria_dei_numeri"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 teoria dei numeri}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Teoria_dei_grafi"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 teoria dei grafi}}. Sembra che {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pierre_Simon_Laplace"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Pierre Simon Laplace}} abbia affermato "Leggete Eulero; egli \'e8 il maestro di tutti noi".
\fs22\fsmilli11200 \cf4 \super \

\fs28 \cf2 \cb1 \nosupersub \
\cb3 Eulero \'e8 stato senz'altro il pi\'f9 grande fornitore di "denominazioni matematiche", offrendo il suo nome a una quantit\'e0 impressionante di formule, teoremi, metodi, criteri, relazioni, equazioni. In geometria: il {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cerchio_di_Feuerbach"}}{\fldrslt 
\f2\i \cf4 cerchio}}, la {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Retta_di_Eulero"}}{\fldrslt 
\f2\i \cf4 retta}} e i 
\f2\i punti di Eulero
\f1\i0  relativi ai triangoli, pi\'f9 la 
\f2\i relazione di Eulero-Slim
\f1\i0 , che riguardava il cerchio circoscritto a un triangolo; nella teoria dei numeri: il {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Criterio_di_Eulero"}}{\fldrslt 
\f2\i \cf4 criterio di Eulero}} e il {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Teorema_di_Eulero_(aritmetica_modulare)"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Teorema di Fermat-Eulero}}, l'
\f2\i indicatore di Eulero
\f1\i0 , l'{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Identit%C3%A0_di_Eulero"}}{\fldrslt 
\f2\i \cf4 identit\'e0 di Eulero}}, la {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Congettura_di_Eulero"}}{\fldrslt 
\f2\i \cf4 congettura di Eulero}}; nella meccanica: gli {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Angoli_di_Eulero"}}{\fldrslt 
\f2\i \cf4 angoli di Eulero}}, il 
\f2\i carico critico di Eulero
\f1\i0  (per instabilit\'e0); nell'analisi: la {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Costante_di_Eulero-Mascheroni"}}{\fldrslt 
\f2\i \cf4 costante di Eulero-Mascheroni}}, la {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Funzione_Gamma"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 funzione gamma}} di Eulero; in logica: il {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagramma_di_Venn"}}{\fldrslt 
\f2\i \cf4 diagramma di Eulero-Venn}}; nella teoria dei grafi: (di nuovo) la 
